# Cursor Rules for RaiseRocket Marketing Website

## 🎯 **Project Context**
- This is a marketing website for RaiseRocket AI salary negotiation tool
- Space/rocket theme with futuristic, bold design
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Dark mode friendly with space-themed gradients

## 🎨 **Design System**
- **Brand Colors**: #164CFF (blue), #FFA500 (orange), #7ED957 (green)
- **Theme**: Space-oriented with rocket, orbit, lunar imagery
- **Typography**: Clean sans-serif with tech feel
- **Gradients**: Blue/orange accent glows and space-themed effects

## 🏗️ **Architecture Guidelines**
- Use Next.js 15 App Router (src/app/ directory)
- Implement server-side rendering where possible
- Use React Server Components for static content
- Client Components only when interactivity is needed
- Follow atomic design principles for components

## 📱 **Component Development**
- **Mobile-First**: Design for mobile, enhance for desktop
- **Chakra UI**: Primary component library with custom theme
- **Responsive**: Use responsive breakpoints consistently
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- **Dark Mode**: Ensure all components work in both themes

## 🚀 **Marketing Features**
- **Hero Section**: "Take Your Salary to the Moon 🚀"
- **Waitlist Form**: Email signup with validation
- **Three-Column Layout**: How It Works section
- **Pricing Tiers**: Orbital (basic) and Lunar ($99/year)
- **Testimonials**: Social proof section
- **FAQ**: Common questions about the service

## 🎭 **UI/UX Standards**
- **Space Illustrations**: Rocket orbit, checklist, handshake icons
- **Gradient Effects**: Blue/orange accent glows
- **Animations**: Smooth transitions with Framer Motion
- **Loading States**: Skeleton screens and spinners
- **Error Handling**: User-friendly error messages

## 🔧 **Code Quality**
- Use TypeScript strictly with proper typing
- Write self-documenting code with clear naming
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations

## 📊 **Performance Goals**
- Lighthouse score > 90
- Core Web Vitals optimization
- Image optimization with Next.js Image
- Bundle size optimization
- Proper caching strategies

## 🌐 **Browser Support**
- Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+
- Mobile browsers: iOS Safari, Chrome Mobile
- Progressive enhancement approach

## 🎯 **User Experience Goals**
- Intuitive navigation and clear CTAs
- Fast loading times (< 3 seconds)
- Smooth animations and transitions
- Clear value proposition
- Easy waitlist signup process
